text: What i ve noticed in relationships where one s love language is touch  hugs  kisses  cuddling  etc  and one s love language isn t physical touch and they tend to stay away from it  In order to be compatible  you will need to learn each other s love language  The one who doesn t express love by physical touch will obviously need more work though  You can t have two people with two different love languages and let one express their love language without letting the other expressing theirs  In this type of relationship it s usually the one who doesn t express love through physical touch that gets their love language across  while not letting the other who loves through physical touch express their language You have to try to work into the other s language though if you truly love them  or it probably won t be a functional relationship
